<IMG ALT="Simplifying the Digital Work World" SRC="images/cover.gif" WIDTH=450 HEIGHT=126>

<P>
<IMG ALT="freeway of technology" SRC="images/cover5.jpg" WIDTH=225 HEIGHT=251 ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT COLOR="#0000FF"><B>From the corporate headquarters to the home office, we share a fast-moving world in 
which companies of all sizes need the reach and effectiveness of a multinational 
organization, but can't lose sight of the disciplines of a small business.</B></FONT><P>

Regardless of our size, we all compete in the same global marketplace. We're subject to the same pressures: 
to deliver service as reliably and quickly; to design, build and ship products with equal 
speed and quality, and to succeed in the same world of dispersed people and distributed 
information.<P>

Today's increasingly digital world offers solutions to two major issues facing 
us all in our efforts to succeed: effectively using ever-growing amounts of information to 
make ourselves and our businesses more effective, and cutting through the information 
clutter to communicate powerfully with customers and others.<P>
This paper is intended to describe Xerox' view of the digital workworld, and to suggest ways that people can use 
technology to simplify their work, be more effective and present themselves with greater 
impact.
<BR><BR>
<A HREF="#top"><B>Top</B></A><P>
